SIMPLE: trine
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trine
<hw>Trine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Trinal</er>.]</ety> <def>Threefold; triple; <as>as, <ex>trine</ex>
dimensions, or length, breadth, and thickness</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trine</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Trine
<hw>Trine</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>trine</ets>,
<ets>trin</ets>. See <er>Trinal</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Astrol.)</fld> <def>The aspect of planets distant from each other
120 degrees, or one third of the zodiac; trigon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In sextile, square, and <qex>trine</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A triad; trinity.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A single <qex>trine</qex> of brazen tortoises.</q> <rj><qau>Mrs.
Browning.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Eternal One, Almighty <qex>Trine</qex>!</q>
<rj><qau>Keble.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trine</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Trine
<hw>Trine</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To put in the aspect of a
trine.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>By fortune he [Saturn] was now to Venus <qex>trined</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trinervate</ent>⟦br⟧
